\n< Serena >Hmmm... I heard it was an orphanage, but it seems

\n< Cecilia >I work as an information broker. Nice to meet you,
Serena-chan.

\n< Cecilia >(Alright? My job this time is to expose that
scumbag Goupil's embezzlement.)

\n< Cecilia >(I will infiltrate the mansion and find evidence.
I want you to be my support.)

\n< Cecilia >(Specifically, I want you to infiltrate his
mansion as a maid.)
\n< Cecilia >(There are three things I want you to do.)

\n< Cecilia >(The first thing is to unlock the window in the
bathroom. I will enter from there.)

\n< Cecilia >(The second thing is to distract the night
patrol.)

\n< Cecilia >(The third thing is the next morning. I will
escape from the second floor, so I need you to
cause a commotion on the first floor to attract
attention.)

\n< Serena >Ugh, I-I'm sorry... This time it's my fault...

\n< Cecilia >Well, I didn't expect everything to go perfectly
either.

\n< Cecilia >Regardless, we were able to retrieve the target
item... the secret ledger. So you could say it was
a success.

\n< Cecilia >But we caused quite a bit of trouble, didn't
we...?

success. I'll write that evaluation on the mission
certificate.

\n< Cecilia >Hmm. Well then, here's the certificate.

\n< Cecilia >Well, I don't think there will be a reward, but
there shouldn't be any penalties either. I think
it's fine to postpone the report to the boss for
now.

\n< Serena >Lady Cecilia... Why did you specifically choose
me?

\n< Serena >There were probably others who could have handled
it better, right?

\n< Cecilia >First, your face. In order to be hired as a maid
at Goupil, you need to have a good-looking face.

\n< Cecilia >If I fail to get hired, I don't know when the next
maid recruitment will be.

\n< Cecilia >That's why it was crucial for the collaborator to
be hired without fail in one shot.
\n< Cecilia >Because you stood out in that aspect.

\n< Cecilia >Well, it's a bit troublesome that my stomach is
like this... but I'm grateful that Goupil didn't
have any restrictions.

\n< Cecilia >And also, don't betray us. It's definitely more
advantageous for you to keep your mouth shut about
Goupil.

\n< Cecilia >That's why it's better to have someone who isn't
rooted in this town. But I still can't trust
someone who is completely rootless.

\n< Cecilia >By narrowing down the conditions like that, you
were the only one who fit perfectly.

\n< Serena >Did you bet on the unicorn incident for that
reason too?

incident?

anyone with a bit of a nose for gossip would know.

\n< Cecilia >It's still a very vague story, like rumors that it
was brought into this town.

\n< Cecilia >So, it's not like I had any concrete evidence or
anything. But you, who is as detached from reality
as the unicorn, came walking right in front of me.

\n< Cecilia >I hope you realize it. When I thought there might
be something, it was a perfect match.

\n< Cecilia >So, if someone finds out about our secret, you
can't just refuse the job like normal. You don't
know what might happen to you.

\n< Cecilia >It would be troublesome for me if you were able to
escape. Well, that kind of trouble was unexpected
though.
\n< Cecilia >Haven't you made enough of an appeal yet?

\n< Cecilia >Don't you have a job you want to ask me, this
capable information broker, Cecilia?

\n< Serena >Yes, I definitely want to ask you. You are the one
I have been looking for.

\n< Serena >Cecilia, the information broker. Lord Valadon.
Please help me find my unicorn... Splendore.
\n< Cecilia >That's right, that's how it has to be.
\n< Cecilia >Thank you for your continued patronage.
